            <summary>Small manuscript for personal use, praising Maṇikarṇika, the famous bathing site especially sacred to the deity Śiva along the Ganges river in the sacred Hindu pilgrimage center, Vārāṇasī. Opens with the second verse of the text as seen in other manuscripts (for example, Ms. Coll. 390, Item 460).</summary>
